**Battle of the Sexes: Multiple Equilibria.** Payoff matrix: (Opera,Opera): $(2,1)$; (Football,Football): $(1,2)$; (Opera,Football) or (Football,Opera): $(0,0)$. \begin{enumerate}[label=(\alph{*})]\item Find all pure strategy Nash equilibria.

\item Find the mixed strategy Nash equilibrium.

\item What is each player's expected payoff at the mixed NE?\end{enumerate}

**Cournot Duopoly.** Two firms, $P = 100-Q$, $Q=q_{1}+q_{2}$, zero marginal cost. \begin{enumerate}[label=(\alph{*})]\item Find each firm's best response function.

\item Find the NE quantities and price.

\item Compare to monopoly and perfect competition.\end{enumerate}
